The Ricci scalar \( R \) is a scalar invariant derived from the Riemann curvature tensor. In Minkowski space, the spacetime is flat, meaning the Riemann curvature tensor vanishes identically in all coordinate systems. Consequently, the Ricci tensor \( R_{\mu\nu} \) and the Ricci scalar \( R \) are also identically zero. This holds in any coordinate system because the vanishing of a tensor in one frame implies its vanishing in all frames due to tensorial transformation properties.

